MA Smith is way too kind as others here will attest
Think outside the box when it comes to recording. If you live in a two party state it is never advisable to record both sides of the conversation. On the other hand, there are shoppers who have learned how to keep their recorder at such a low volume only their own voices can be heard. Your memory can be triggered by many things you say. Another option is to use it immediately after you are finished with an interaction or have left the premises. In those cases simply dictate the major points you need to remember.
Equal rights for others does not mean fewer rights for you. It's not pie.
Never try to teach a pig to sing. It's a waste of your time and it really annoys the pig.

thread.title: Water crisis in wards 13 and 14
thread.title_full: Water crisis in wards 13 and 14

posts.author: thehitavada.com
posts.title: Water crisis in wards 13 and 14
posts.text:
Staff Reporter,
Due to leakage of water pipeline near Arvind Vihar petrol pump this problem is arising and now we are geared up to give petition to concerned officers in Bhopal Municipal Corporation (BMC) to rectify the issue. Uma Shankar Tiwari convenor of local Baghmugaliya Samiti from Baghmugaliya said that around 30-40 thousand residents are staying at ward number 13 and 14 who are suffering because of water crisis. It’s been three days but water supply has not been resumed. We are also geared up to give petition to BMC officials so that measures can be chalked to avert water crisis.
As of now the residents are calling private water tankers as even hand pumps are not in working condition in the nearby region.
It has to be noted that earlier also the Baghmugaliya extension colony is facing serious issues of water crisis problem. In last one week the residents over here are not getting regular supply of water due to improper functioning of water motor pump. Ahmedpur Narmada line’s old water pump motor hardly works which is making the problems of the residents more problematic.
The residents from Baghmugaliya Samiti said had faced this problem even during summer season.
Besides, residents also complaint about the bad road connectivity in the region which is making their life very tough. The potholes are also infringement of health rights of common people. Light rain shower worsen the situation as it is difficult to drive on such dilapidated roads, especially during rains. It gets difficult to judge the potholes and pits in night due to inundation of road by rainwater. Stary dog menace is also an issue which requires attention.
One of the local resident Karishma said that we are not getting regularly water supply because of which now we had to depend on mineral water bottle. Commuters are having a tough time while crossing the roads on their vehicles as they are clueless about the potholes that the incessant rainfall had created on the roads, which also poses a threat to life.
Residents also claimed that the roads in Bhopal are not in accordance with the criteria decided by Indian Road Congress (IRC) and people are facing various problems because of this.
The dismal condition of roads, poor water supply is a denial of exercising right to life with human dignity and we are geared up to approach to Human Rights Commission if proper water electricity is not supplied to the colony. Buying mineral water bottle and depending on private water tanks adds on the burden especially to students who are staying in colony.

SELECT E.LastName, E.FirstName
FROM (Employees AS E
INNER JOIN EmployeeTerritories AS ET ON E.EmployeeID = ET.EmployeeID)
INNER JOIN Territories AS T ON  T.TerritoryID = ET.TerritoryID
WHERE T.TerritoryDescription IN ('Boston', 'Orlando', 'Santa Cruz')
ORDER BY E.LastName;

thread.section_title: Mystery Shopping Forum :: Mystery Shopping Discussion
thread.title: Has anyone ever used a recording device to conduct a shop?
thread.title_full: Has anyone ever used a recording device to conduct a shop?

posts.author: MA Smith
posts.text:
I thought of another thing I do, which came from remedial study when I went back to college. I had too much fun the first time around. I had to do a few, oh alright maybe more than a few classes over.
Anyways, back to the point. I was taught to write down & listen for key words during my classes that would help me write my notes after my classes. The keywords trigger your memory. This takes time but if you can train your brain, it saves time. Key words don't need to be anything for the associate or the shop. A key word/phrase for me could be baby screaming. This reminds me how the associate was smiling & doing everything right when everyone wanted to tell the kid's Mommy to give it a bottle, etc.
My handwritten notes are on steno pads. Dollar General has the best for $1 plus tax.
Use your smartphone if you have a decent data plan. You'd be surprised how filling out the yes and no's will trigger your memory after a 15 hour day.
If it helps we all forget details. My favorite is when I walk into the shop and didn't write down the start time, turn on my voice recorder or use GeoVerify. Another is when I'm so happy to be done with a town that I forget to write down how many customers were waiting in line.at my last shop.
The good news it gets easier to remember details. You will find yourself looking for all the yes and no's on your personal shopping.
Live your life in such a way that when your feet hit the floor in the morning; the devil shudders...And yells OH #%*+! SHE'S AWAKE!
